I"#<ol>
  <li>Cut the halloumi in half crossways, then cut each piece in half horizontally. Place flour on a plate and season with salt and pepper.</li>
  <li>Place the rocket, onion and olives in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Combine vinegar, extra virgin olive oil and oregano in a small bowl. Drizzle over the salad. Toss to combine.</li>
  <li>Heat olive oil in a large non-stick frying pan over medium heat. Add the halloumi and cook for 2 minutes each side or until crisp and golden.</li>
  <li>Serve with lemon wedges.</li>
</ol>
